<TITLE> Tara Gandhi for love, forgiveness </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Noakhali, June 3 (bdnews24.com) -- Tara Gandhi, the grand daughter of Mahatma Gandhi, says human beings are disturbed by fear and environment pollution of different dimensions. She said: "Pity, love and forgiveness can overcome them." Tara was speaking at a discussion as the chief guest at BRDB auditorium in Noakhali town on Thursday evening. Gandhi Ashram Trust organised the discussion. Vice-chairperson of Delhi-based Gandhi's Memory and Philosophy Association, she narrated his experience after visiting Gandhi Ashram (shelter) of Noakhali. Tara said: "I'm overwhelmed to see the respect of the people here for Gandhi's ideology." Chaired by Jharna Chowdhury, the discussion was also addressed among others by former MP Fazle Elahi, Noakhali Press Club president Alamgir Yusuf and educationist Basna Sen Gupta. bdnews
